title.19: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #7
title.93: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #6

description.0: The Hulk fights for Betty Ross' very soul!
description.1: Iron Man tries to free Madame Masque from Hydra, and runs headlong into Hydra's special hired hand- the Hulk!
description.4: When Eric Masterson is fatally wounded by Mongoose, Thor pleads with his father to spare the mortal. Odin agrees--but his condition will change Thor's world forever!
description.6: Still trapped on a war-ravaged planet, Archangel must fight for his life in an arena of death!
description.8: IT'S A DREAM! IT'S A HOAX! IT'S AN IMAGINARY STORY! AND - IT'S ULTRON! The FF beholds Reed Richards' dream of an attack by Ultron.
description.9: Missing X-Man Polaris has sent out an S.O.S to her fellow X-Men at their Australian base. Her teammates follow her call for help only to be led into the hands of Savage Land mutates, under the rule of the Sorceress Zaladane!
description.13: Has Paladin gone crazy? He's hired himself out to Carlton Drake and his Life Foundation!
description.14: The Life Foundation is involved in a conspiracy that threatens world peace. To stop its leader, Carlton Drake, Spider-Man forms an uneasy alliance with Silver Sable and the man she hired to stop the Life Foundation- Paladin!
description.15: No longer under Jinku's control, the reformed Lava Men help the Avengers get Gilgamesh to safety. Gilgamesh is beyond the aid of mortal medicine, and the team must turn to the Eternal Sersi to save their fallen teammate.
description.16: There's a Bloodstone fragment in South America. And to get it, Captain America must survive 'The Wheel of Death!' USAGENT VERSUS SCOURGE Part II USAgent discovers just how deadly Scourge really is!
description.18: The tragic secret of Midnight is revealed!
description.22: Conan must face the wheel of life and death!
description.23: The connection between the original Human Torch and Vision laid out in full...all thanks to Scarlet Witch! Tigra continues to transform into her most animalistic self, while the Avengers struggle to keep up with all this change. Tigra gets a dose of Pym particles, but why?
description.24: Spider-Man's black alien suit from Secret Wars ends up taking over its host...permanently!
description.28: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #132. ""Strangers on a Lift."" Dazzler faces an intimidating threat while on an elevator ride to the top floor of a parking garage.
description.30: Co-starring Franklin Richards! Reed and Sue Richards’ son aids the Power Pack in their clean-up of harmful toxic waste!
description.31: Captain America and Diamondback travel from Subterranea to South America in a desperate attempt to get one of the Bloodstone fragments before Baron Zemo does! USAGENT VERSUS SCOURGE Part I: Scourge is out to kill the Power Broker!
description.34: Mephisto and Satannish are locked in combat -- and New York is caught in the crossfire! Only one person can help Doctor Strange now -- the legendary AGAMOTTO!
description.36: Blackheart is a creature made from all the despair and evil the world can offer. On an isolated hill, soaked in memories of painful pasts, Blackheart is born. Daredevil fights his strangest villain yet. Guest-starring Spider-Man!
description.37: It's a real-life fairytale when our heroes are transported to Earth-1193, a medieval version of Britain! Kitty is captured by an evil ogre along with Princess Catherine. Will the damsels be saved by their knights in shining armor and have their "happily ever after's"?
description.38: Hulk comes face to face with Satan himself!
description.39: There's a new Madam Masque in charge of the Maggia, and her orders are to kill the crippled Tony Stark! As if that wasn't enough trouble for America's favorite playboy, Tony's also being targeted by the Dreadnaught and an elite team of A.I.M. agents!
description.42: In the Black Galaxy, Thor comes face to face with another old foe--Celestials! Will the Odinson be able to survive another duel with these godlike beings, when the last nearly claimed his life?
description.44: The team finds themselves on a distant planet, ravaged by war. When X-Factor is split, can they make their way back together and off the wartorn planet?
description.46: Aron the Rogue Watcher has captured the Fantastic Four, using their dreams for his own mysteriousplans! His first victim - Susan Storm, the Invisible Woman!
description.47: Donald Pierce has assembled a group of mutant-hating baddies known as The Reavers. With his dangerous crew, Pierce has devised new strategies to terrorize mutants...and he's putting those methods in practice. Meanwhile, Longshot is having some strange dreams that lead him on a spirit journey.
description.51: She-Hulk and Captain America are all brawn, no strategy, as they attempt to save Scarlet Witch from the mental manipulations of a mutant! Who is the mutant possessing Wanda's powerful mind? And when Scarlet Witch  begins to enjoy the lack of control, will She-Hulk and Cap be able to talk her into reason? Scarlet Witch's hex powers at their unhinged worst!
description.52: What if Steve Rogers refused to give up being Captain America? John Walker is the handpicked successor for the Captain America title, but this Steve Rogers refuses to become Nomad and decides to fight instead!
description.53: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #131. ""Was Not What Will Be."" Disco star Dazzler takes the stage as she struggles between her Super Hero and popstar life!
description.54: Gang leader Damage and his crew of lackeys play Punisher for a fool...and sorely regret the mistake. Punisher's determined to get the drop on Damage- and whatever Punisher wants, Punisher gets.
description.55: The Scorpion's back- and he's got a new, deadlier tail! Scorpion's been hired to kidnap someone, but Scorpion turns the job into a plot to kidnap J. Jonah Jameson. Trouble is, the Jameson he tries to catch is really the Chameleon!
description.56: Scorpion has double-crossed Justin Hammer. That's why the Rhino and Backlash are out to kill him- and why Spidey must save the Scorpion!
description.57: Paladin has a new client- Carlton Drake of the Life Foundation! Is money the only reason why Paladin's working for him? Spidey's out to find the answer to that, and to why Carlton Drake is secretly stocking his camp with every gun he can lay hands on! Guest-starring Silver Sable!
description.58: The Avengers continue to battle Jinku in a red-hot lava fight. Invisible Woman attempts to save the Hyrdobase from a lava column. Plus, a hero takes a near fatal blow!
description.59: The teen-aged Captain America must stop the terror of Mother Night and the new Sisters of Sin! And in the prologue to the six-part "Bloodstone Hunt" saga, Diamondback must stop both Baron Zemo and Batroc's Brigade from stealing the skeleton of Ulysses Bloodstone!
description.61: He's Moon Knight's old foe, Midnight! At least, that's what Moon Knight thinks!
description.64: Conan must retrieve a sacred relic stolen by a fanatic cult. The only way he can succeed is if he slays every member of the cult!
description.67: As Baron Mordo pushes Doctor Strange to his absolute limits, the unthinkable happens -- Mordo summons MEPHISTO! Or maybe one of his closest kin?
description.68: Havok goes after Leila's capturers; T'Challa sets out to rescue Miyo Moshigo, and more! Note: this contains the Black Panther, Hulk, and Coldblood stories from the original issue.
description.69: Hornhead's travels on the road continue! DD must save a mutant girl from being apprehended. But when Blob and Pyro of the Brotherhood of Mutants show up to claim their "prize", all bets are off! Blob and Pyro behave badly, and DD delivers a lesson in bar etiquette neither will soon forget!
description.70: Nigel Frobisher is the newest servant to Courtney Ross! Meanwhile, Excalibur tricks their evil counterparts...or so they believe.
description.71: Hulk vs. the Necrophage: Round 2! Plus: Cloot's true identity revealed!
description.72: Tony Stark, now paralyzed from the waist down, must come to terms with living his life without walking ever again. Can the once invincible Iron Man find solidarity amongst his fellow Avengers? Plus: Iron Man flies again!
description.75: Count Tagar is revealed as the Mongoose's mysterious leader! He gives Thor a mission- to free Hercules and the High Evolutionary from the Black Galaxy. Can even a Thunder God survive such a deadly task?
description.77: X-Factor and their ship are transported to a different place…is this the work of the Celestials?
description.79: No mercy for the mole man! The clones of the Fantastic Four created by Aron the Rogue Watcher, attempt to kill the Mole man who is taken surprise by the attack. Did they awaken the anger in him?
description.80: The Sentinels, including Master Mold, are creating quite a few issues for the X-team. An epic battle ensues that threatens the stability of the team. It's Mutant versus Sentinel...and the outcome will surprise you.
description.84: What if Daredevil killed the Kingpin? This alternate reality picks up from the events of “Born Again,” but this time Matt Murdock is driven to murder Wilson Fisk.
description.85: Note: this issue does not collect reprinted material from UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #130. ""Outside In."" Moira MacTaggert seeks a scientific miracle to resurrect her son, Proteus. Guest-starring Banshee.
description.89: Power Pack cleans up the ocean as part of a super-powered, planetary crusade!
description.90: Marvel's First Family guest-stars! Why is Death's Head dusting up with the Fantastic Four? And in which timeline?!
description.92: Moon Knight needs to go through an entire army if he wants to bring Bushman to justice!
description.95: Conan becomes the unwitting pawn of one man's obsession for gold. The man will learn that the price for tricking Conan is paid in blood!
description.96: Hawkeye and the Orb are uneasy allies as they try to escape from the clutches of Plantman.  Plus, Starfox in solo action!
description.97: The origin of the lava men revealed! The Avengers are trapped inside a lava ball by Jinku, the lava mens' witch doctor. Will Sub Mariner be able to bail his teammates out of this bind?
description.98: Cap makes his move to bust up the Sisters of Sin's vicious hate camp for kids! But has he already been irrevocably infected by the hatred he plans to stamp out?
description.99: Hawkeye discovers someone is using the Avengers name without permission! It's up to him and Mockingbird to go investigate!

2.text: Contains Panther’s Quest Part 17: Lost Promises Part 2 and Quasar in "It Came From Within". PANTHER’S QUEST PART 17: T’Challa thinks he’s finally going to get some answers out of Patrick Slade, but Elmer Gore catches up with him.

3.text: This is it! The New Mutants fateful throw down with Hela for the fate of Asgard! Will Mirage and the Valkyrior be free of Hel’s seductive grasp?

10.text: Wolverine and company get the story behind the Gehenna Stone: a millennia-old tale of warring gods that starts in the Middle East and leads straight to Madripoor!

12.text: Captain Reptyl joins Skrulls! Shalla Bal is kidnapped by the Kree! And the Silver Surfer can’t stop the war from happening!

17.text: She-Hulk is NASA's celebrity guest of their brand new facility! Who says being the She-Hulk doesn't come with its perks?

19.text: Following last arc's skirmish you’ll be surprised to learn that…Cloak's alive!?

20.text: The Punisher takes on the Shadowmasters! But will this team of ninja assassins end up becoming Frank Castle’s allies?

21.text: Learn the extraordinary origin of the Shadowmasters, a clan of ninja assassins seeking to restore their native Japan following the devastation of WWII. But do the Shadowmasters represent a new brand of hero…or vigilante?

27.text: It all comes down to this! Doctor Strange casts a last-ditch spell to stop the dueling demons Mephisto and Satannish from destroying all of reality!

29.text: The Sub-Mariner tells his side of the story behind his team-up with Doctor Doom. Plus, the saga concludes with the untimely death of Marrina, Namor’s beloved.

32.text: Wolverine and Jessica Drew follow an unstable adventurer on a chase through San Francisco! A nest of blood-drinkers is waiting for them, and so is someone worse

33.text: S.H.I.E.L.D. as you know it may be gone, and that's bad news for Earth and Nick Fury! There's a new danger stalking Nick; to stop it, he must band with trusted allies inclduing Alphonso "Mac" Mackenzie, and the alluring Contessa Valentina Allegra de la Fontaine!

34.text: Mephisto and Satannish are locked in combat -- and New York is caught in the crossfire! Only one person can help Doctor Strange now -- the legendary AGAMOTTO!

35.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 16: Lost Promises. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 16: Amid the turf war between the Fathers and the Comrads, T’Challa and Zanti try to get urgent medical care for Theodore from a whites-only clinic.

40.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 15: Last Night I Wept for Freedom. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 15: A group of anti-apartheid radicals calling themselves the Fathers comes to the aid of T’Challa and attacks the Comrads.

41.text: The kids get resourceful when trying to escape Asgard’s most hellish realms. Mirage becomes Hela’s puppet of death.

48.text: Everything happens to Wolverine, except when it happens to his friends! Madripoor pilot Archie Corrigan's brother Burt is hip-deep in pseudo-vampires, and there's only one man qualified to claw his way out! The Gehenna Stone Affair begins here!

50.text: The Badoon attack the Skrulls. Clumsy Foulup betrays the Skrulls to the Kree. Captain Reptyl betrays his crew. The Stranger arrives. The Silver Surfer tries to stop the cosmos-threatening chaos. And, in the middle of it all, the Contemplator appears – or does he?

60.text: Jennifer thinks it's just an average Saturday morning watching cartoons until she's randomly transported into the television itself! Featuring several epic cartoon parodies!

62.text: Prelude to the SHADOWMASTERS limited series! Frank Castle must eliminate the head of a secret society of ninjas. But the Eternal Sun Society proves indefatigable!

63.text: Circus elephants exposed to a nuclear bomb give birth to super-powered pachyderms: Electralux, Mammoth, Trunklops and Rumbo!

65.text: Death’s Head is hired on an assassin’s contract…and Iron Man of 2020 may be the only one who can halt the hit!

66.text: Before she was a New Warrior, she was an Atlantean! Enter…Namorita!

67.text: As Baron Mordo pushes Doctor Strange to his absolute limits, the unthinkable happens -- Mordo summons MEPHISTO! Or maybe one of his closest kin?

68.text: Contains Panther’s Quest Part 14: Somebody’s Going to Pay and Hulk in Splashdown. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 14: T’Challa attempts to rescue Miyo Moshigo from the Comrads.

73.text: Contains only Panther’s Quest Part 13: A Right to Kill. PANTHER’S QUEST PART 13: Chikane takes T’Challa to the home of Miyo Moshigo as they hide from the South African authorities.

74.text: As if the battle with Freedom Force from last issue wasn’t enough, now the New Mutants must confront the wrath of Hela! Doctor Strange guest-stars!

81.text: The flashback that's still starting storylines: one of Wolverine's earliest battles with Sabretooth! Decades ago, innocents paid the price for Sabretooth's hatred of Logan! Will history repeat itself in present-day Madripoor?

83.text: The Silver Surfer versus a Skrull that walks like a Kree!

86.text: Scarlet Witch has a stalker on her trail, and she's terrified for her life! Who is this mysterious being watching her every move? And will the Witch be able to rely on the reconfigured Vision if she's truly down and out?

87.text: Damage Control is recruited to clean-up Xavier’s School for Gifted Mutants. But as soon as Damage Control repairs, the Professor’s mutants destroy! Wolverine gets “pied” and laughter does not ensue.

91.text: Jennifer Walters takes on one of the biggest challenges that face all of us! The dreaded job interview!

93.text: Dagger struggles to adjust to her new condition and ever-changing abilities.

94.text: The Punisher is reacquainted with fear when he meets the heir of the last true ninja in an underground training camp!

99.text: Hawkeye discovers someone is using the Avengers name without permission! It's up to him and Mockingbird to go investigate!
